    "body": "Ideally this is handled in Ganache , but I'm not sure how long we'll be waiting for that so probably best to assume it isn't an option.\r\n\r\nI like the idea and I can see the use case.  But with a dedicated `increase_nonce` function I'm unsure how to the transaction history and `rpc.undo` functionality. Should the empty transactions be included in the history and the undo buffer? Or better to be collectively batched as a single action, somehow? I lean towards the latter but I'm not sure what it looks like.\r\n\r\nExposing `silent` within `Account.transfer` is a very simple solution and makes it easy for the user to run a for loop..  at which point they should be well aware of the consequences of the action re: the history.",
