    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Agreed. Do you think batching the transactions would have any benefits other than it potentially being one history element? If batching does not lead to a performance increase or another tangible benefit, then I see little reason to implement it. \r\n\r\nIn my use case, I need to get the nonce of some addresses to high double / low tripple digit numbers to deploy contracts at addresses with specific properties (like only being 15bytes instead of 20bytes long). I would already be very happy to have `silent` exposed to suppress the console output and if eventually this can be done faster via ganache, that would be awesome!",
